# Commit Message Template
# 
# Format: <type>(<scope>): <subject>
# 
# Types:
#   feat:     A new feature
#   fix:      A bug fix
#   docs:     Documentation only changes
#   style:    Changes that don't affect code meaning (formatting, etc)
#   refactor: Code change that neither fixes a bug nor adds a feature
#   perf:     Performance improvement
#   test:     Adding missing tests
#   chore:    Changes to build process or auxiliary tools
#   version:  Version bump
#
# Scope: Optional, can be anything specifying the place of the commit change
#
# Subject: Short description (50 chars or less)
#
# Body: Detailed explanation (72 chars per line)
#
# Footer: References to issues, breaking changes, etc.